This paper is primarily focused on generating images using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a popular technique in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a recurrent generative model, which is a type of neural network architecture that falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses a way to quantitatively compare adversarial networks, which could be considered a graph theory (cs.GR) problem.
